  <title>Clutter.ClickAction::clicked</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(click_action, actor, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>The ::clicked signal is emitted when the <link xref="Clutter.Actor">Clutter.Actor</link> to which
a <link xref="Clutter.ClickAction">Clutter.ClickAction</link> has been applied should respond to a
pointer button press and release events</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>click_action :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.ClickAction that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>actor :</p></td>
<td><p>the <link xref="Clutter.Actor">Clutter.Actor</link> attached to the @action</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.4</p>
